input.content: Answer the following questions as concisely as possible.
Who played the girl elf in the hobbit?

data.sampled:
Cate Blanchett; Galadriel Celeborn[1][2] was a Noldo in exile,[3][4][5] the wife of Fellowship leader for the Longbeards and Lothlóriën Lord Celeborn and with him the co-ruler of the kingdom of Eryn Lasgalen to the east of the Misty Mountains.
As a kinswoman of Noldorin king Gil-galad and a co-ruler with Noldorin Sinda Celebrimbor she was one of the most influential Noldor in Middle-earth after the Second Age.[6] [7][8]
With her husband she was forced to flee Eregion and abandon Eryn Lasgalen after the fall of Angmar at the Battle of Fornost. [ 9][10][11][12]
After the War of the Ring in 3441, upon the advice of their former liege-lord and friend Gildor, Celeborn and Celebrian left Middle-earth together with Elrond.[13]
With an air of mystery the books do not specify why they remained in Middle-earth despite having forsaken their kingdom and their people, why they went into exile with Galadriel, whether they met on the way to Grey Havens, and if so why they parted ways afterwards.[14][15]
Cate Blanchett did not audition or screen test for the role; director Peter Jackson chose her based on her performance in Elizabeth (1998), which he had seen on a plane trip.[16]
